<title>SOUTH AFRICA: TABLE - DELTA HALF YEAR SHR EDGES UP.</title>
<headline>TABLE - DELTA HALF YEAR SHR EDGES UP.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended June 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		48.5	  vs 39.5</p>
<p>    - attrib		  45.0	  vs 42.7</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 14.5	  vs 12.5</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   20.15	 vs 19.12</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   34.33	 vs 31.58</p>
<p>    Tax			 12.76	 vs 11.09</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   0.75	  vs 2.31 received</p>
<p>    Turnover		  333.43	vs 246.34</p>
<p>    Exceptional items     1.81 loss   vs 1.47 gain</p>
<p>Div payable September 19</p>
<p>on register August 22</p>
<p>Full name: Delta Electrical Industries Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Delta said in a statement that shareholders could elect to receive capitalisation shares instead of a cash dividend.</p>
<p>It added that growth in the second half of the year is expected to be in line with that seen in the first half.</p>
